{
  "dialogueGraphs": [
    {
      "id": "DG_SCN069_COPIER_EVIDENCE_PACKET",
      "sceneId": "SCN-069",
      "startNodeId": "N_START_01",
      "nodes": [
        {
          "id": "N_START_01",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
          "conditions": [
            {
              "key": "act3.evidencePacketCompiled",
              "op": "==",
              "value": false
            },
            {
              "key": "act3.recordsEvidenceCollected",
              "op": "==",
              "value": true
            }
          ],
          "text": "The Copy and Fax Room smells like warm plastic and old toner. (pause)\nThe copier\u2019s control panel is lit, patient, and already disappointed in you.",
          "next": "N_START_02"
        },
        {
          "id": "N_START_02",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
          "text": "You have the records. You don\u2019t have a packet anyone can sign without becoming the story.",
          "next": "N_PANEL_01"
        },
        {
          "id": "N_PANEL_01",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
          "text": "The screen offers three big buttons: COPY, SCAN and \u201cCOMPLIANCE DUPLICATION (LEGACY).\u201d (pause) Under them, a smaller note: \u201cDO NOT CREATE NEW INFORMATION.\u201d (pause) Someone has underlined it hard enough to dent the plastic.",
          "next": "N_PANEL_02"
        },
        {
          "id": "N_PANEL_02",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
          "text": "The copier beeps once\u2014an opinion. (pause)\nOn-screen: \u201cSELECT SOURCE MATERIAL.\u201d (pause)\nBelow that: \u201cORIGINALS ONLY.\u201d (pause)\nBelow that, smaller: \u201cDO NOT FEED ORIGINALS.\u201d (pause)\n\nA problem designed by committee, maintained by habit.",
          "next": "N_PANEL_03"
        },
        {
          "id": "N_PANEL_03",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
          "text": "It waits for a choice like an auditor.",
          "next": "PC_MAIN_MENU"
        },
        {
          "id": "PC_MAIN_MENU",
          "type": "player_choice",
          "speakerId": "PLAYER",
          "choices": [
            {
              "id": "USE_COMPILE",
              "text": "use: Compile Evidence Packet section.",
              "next": "PC_COMPILE_APPROACH_STD"
            },
            {
              "id": "USE_TEST",
              "text": "use: Run a test page first.",
              "next": "N_TEST_01"
            },
            {
              "id": "LOOK_CHECKLIST",
              "text": "look: Review the packet checklist posted on the wall.",
              "next": "N_CHECKLIST_01"
            },
            {
              "id": "USE_SERVICE_CODE",
              "text": "use: Use service code / compliance duplication mode.",
              "checks": [
                {
                  "type": "faction",
                  "faction": "OLEA"
                }
              ],
              "onPassNext": "N_COMPLIANCE_01",
              "onFailNext": "N_SERVICE_DENIED_01"
            },
            {
              "id": "USE_FAX_REDUNDANCY",
              "text": "use: Fax it \u201cfor redundancy.\u201d",
              "next": "N_FAX_01"
            },
            {
              "id": "ASK_WHICH",
              "text": "ask: \u201cWhich is it.\u201d",
              "next": "N_WHICH_01"
            },
            {
              "id": "LOOK_STICKERS",
              "text": "look: Service code sticker stack.",
              "next": "N_STICKERS_01"
            },
            {
              "id": "LOOK_FAX_TRAY",
              "text": "look: Fax machine tray.",
              "next": "N_FAXTRAY_01"
            },
            {
              "id": "LOOK_BINDER_SHELF",
              "text": "look: Binder supplies shelf.",
              "next": "N_SHELF_01"
            },
            {
              "id": "LEAVE",
              "text": "leave: Step away.",
              "next": "N_LEAVE_01"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "id": "N_WHICH_01",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
          "text": "The copier won\u2019t answer questions.\nIt waits for choice, like an auditor with the finding written.",
          "next": "PC_MAIN_MENU"
        },
        {
          "id": "N_STICKERS_01",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
          "text": "A neat stack of peel-off stickers: SERVICE ACCESS / CALIBRATION / AUDIT OVERRIDE (EXPIRED). (pause) They\u2019re numbered, implying a calendar you\u2019re not invited to see.",
          "next": "PC_MAIN_MENU"
        },
        {
          "id": "N_FAXTRAY_01",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
          "text": "The fax tray holds one curled confirmation page from years ago. (pause) It reads: \u201cTRANSMISSION PARTIAL \u2014 RECEIPT SUCCESSFUL.\u201d (pause) Someone circled \u201cSUCCESSFUL,\u201d like it won an argument.",
          "next": "PC_MAIN_MENU"
        },
        {
          "id": "N_SHELF_01",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
          "text": "Binders, tabs, label maker: tape bay open.\nTwo fonts: \u201cOFFICIAL\u201d; \u201cOFFICIAL (CONDENSED).\u201d\nThe second looks nervous.",
          "next": "PC_MAIN_MENU"
        },
        {
          "id": "N_CHECKLIST_01",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
          "text": "A laminated checklist hangs beside the panel. (pause) Edges browned from fluorescent light. (pause) Line 4 reads: \u201cCross-check identifiers, dates, and recurring charges.\u201d (pause) Line 5 reads: \u201cDo not editorialize. Editorialization is discoverable.\u201d (pause) In pen someone added: \u201cIf it feels like a story it isn\u2019t evidence.\u201d (pause) The handwriting gets smaller on the last words. (pause) Like it\u2019s trying not to be quoted.",
          "next": "PC_CHECKLIST_BACK"
        },
        {
          "id": "PC_CHECKLIST_BACK",
          "type": "player_choice",
          "speakerId": "PLAYER",
          "choices": [
            {
              "id": "LEAVE_BACK",
              "text": "leave: Back to the panel.",
              "next": "PC_MAIN_MENU"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "id": "N_TEST_01",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
          "text": "You feed a blank sheet. (pause) Your hand hesitates for no reason you\u2019d put in writing. (pause) The machine pulls it in like it\u2019s taking custody.",
          "next": "N_TEST_02"
        },
        {
          "id": "N_TEST_02",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
          "text": "It prints: \u201cTEST PAGE \u2014 NOT RECORD.\u201d (pause)\nIn the corner: a timestamp accurate to the second, daring you to dispute it. (pause)\nThe copier is warmed up. (pause)\nThe room is warm too, in its own quiet way.",
          "next": "PC_TEST_MENU"
        },
        {
          "id": "PC_TEST_MENU",
          "type": "player_choice",
          "speakerId": "PLAYER",
          "choices": [
            {
              "id": "USE_COMPILE_NOW",
              "text": "use: Compile Evidence Packet section.",
              "next": "PC_COMPILE_APPROACH_STD"
            },
            {
              "id": "USE_SERVICE_CODE_NOW",
              "text": "use: Use service code / compliance duplication mode.",
              "checks": [
                {
                  "type": "faction",
                  "faction": "OLEA"
                }
              ],
              "onPassNext": "N_COMPLIANCE_01",
              "onFailNext": "N_SERVICE_DENIED_01"
            },
            {
              "id": "LEAVE_BACK",
              "text": "leave: Back to the panel menu.",
              "next": "PC_MAIN_MENU"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "id": "N_SERVICE_DENIED_01",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
          "text": "The panel requests an authorization code you do not possess. (pause) It offers a helpful explanation: \u201cUNAUTHORIZED USE CREATES DISCOVERABLE INTENT.\u201d",
          "next": "PC_SERVICE_DENIED_BACK"
        },
        {
          "id": "PC_SERVICE_DENIED_BACK",
          "type": "player_choice",
          "speakerId": "PLAYER",
          "choices": [
            {
              "id": "LEAVE_BACK",
              "text": "leave: \u201cFine.\u201d",
              "next": "PC_MAIN_MENU"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "id": "N_COMPLIANCE_01",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
          "text": "You peel a SERVICE ACCESS sticker. The adhesive resists, personally.\nPanel accepts the code without gratitude.",
          "next": "N_COMPLIANCE_02"
        },
        {
          "id": "N_COMPLIANCE_02",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
          "text": "New options: \u201cWATERMARK: WORKING COPY,\u201d \u201cAUTO-REDACT PERSONAL,\u201d \u201cMATCH LEDGER FORMAT.\u201d Not about truth. About survivability.",
          "next": "PC_COMPLIANCE_MENU"
        },
        {
          "id": "PC_COMPLIANCE_MENU",
          "type": "player_choice",
          "speakerId": "PLAYER",
          "choices": [
            {
              "id": "USE_COMPILE",
              "text": "use: Compile Evidence Packet section.",
              "next": "PC_COMPILE_APPROACH_COMP"
            },
            {
              "id": "USE_TEST",
              "text": "use: Run a test page first.",
              "next": "N_TESTC_01"
            },
            {
              "id": "LEAVE_TO_STANDARD",
              "text": "leave: Return to standard menu.",
              "next": "PC_MAIN_MENU"
            },
            {
              "id": "LEAVE",
              "text": "leave: Step away.",
              "next": "N_LEAVE_01"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "id": "N_TESTC_01",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
          "text": "In compliance mode, even a blank page feels like a form. (pause) The machine prints: \u201cTEST PAGE \u2014 NOT RECORD,\u201d (pause) then adds a subtle watermark you didn\u2019t ask for.",
          "next": "PC_TESTC_BACK"
        },
        {
          "id": "PC_TESTC_BACK",
          "type": "player_choice",
          "speakerId": "PLAYER",
          "choices": [
            {
              "id": "USE_COMPILE",
              "text": "use: Compile Evidence Packet section.",
              "next": "PC_COMPILE_APPROACH_COMP"
            },
            {
              "id": "LEAVE_BACK",
              "text": "leave: Back.",
              "next": "PC_COMPLIANCE_MENU"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "id": "PC_COMPILE_APPROACH_STD",
          "type": "player_choice",
          "speakerId": "PLAYER",
          "choices": [
            {
              "id": "USE_CAREFUL",
              "text": "use: Compile carefully (cross-check identifiers, dates, recurring charges).",
              "next": "N_COMPILE_CAREFUL_STD_01"
            },
            {
              "id": "USE_FAST",
              "text": "use: Compile fast (accept defaults).",
              "next": "N_COMPILE_FAST_STD_01"
            },
            {
              "id": "LEAVE_BACK",
              "text": "leave: Not yet.",
              "next": "PC_MAIN_MENU"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "id": "PC_COMPILE_APPROACH_COMP",
          "type": "player_choice",
          "speakerId": "PLAYER",
          "choices": [
            {
              "id": "USE_CAREFUL",
              "text": "use: Compile carefully (use compliance formatting, verify every field).",
              "next": "N_COMPILE_CAREFUL_COMP_01"
            },
            {
              "id": "USE_FAST",
              "text": "use: Compile fast (let compliance mode decide).",
              "next": "N_COMPILE_FAST_COMP_01"
            },
            {
              "id": "LEAVE_BACK",
              "text": "leave: Not yet.",
              "next": "PC_COMPLIANCE_MENU"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "id": "N_COMPILE_CAREFUL_STD_01",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
          "text": "You lay out the records evidence and build a packet that can\u2019t be argued with easily. (pause)\nIdentifiers. Dates. Recurring charges. (pause)\nThe same numbers showing up where they shouldn\u2019t.",
          "next": "N_COMPILE_PRINT_01"
        },
        {
          "id": "N_COMPILE_FAST_STD_01",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
          "text": "You accept the defaults and feed the machine what it wants. (pause) If anything\u2019s wrong, it\u2019s wrong in a standard way. (pause) Sometimes that passes as defensible.",
          "next": "N_COMPILE_PRINT_01"
        },
        {
          "id": "N_COMPILE_CAREFUL_COMP_01",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
          "text": "You let compliance mode format the output, but you don\u2019t let it think for you. (pause) You verify every identifier, every date and every repeating charge. (pause) Survivability without improvisation.",
          "next": "N_COMPILE_PRINT_01"
        },
        {
          "id": "N_COMPILE_FAST_COMP_01",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
          "text": "You let compliance mode decide. (pause)\nIt watermarks what it can and redacts what it thinks is personal. (pause)\nIt aligns everything to the ledger\u2019s idea of reality. (pause)\nIt\u2019s not truth. (pause)\nIt\u2019s presentation with guardrails.",
          "next": "N_COMPILE_PRINT_01"
        },
        {
          "id": "N_COMPILE_PRINT_01",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
          "text": "The copier pulls page after page, stamping the corner with a bland, official certainty. (pause)\nThe sound is steady. (pause)\nYour jaw isn\u2019t.",
          "next": "N_COMPILE_PRINT_02"
        },
        {
          "id": "N_COMPILE_PRINT_02",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
          "text": "A tab prints last: \u201cEVIDENCE PACKET \u2014 RECORDS.\u201d\nThe label maker chooses \u201cOFFICIAL (CONDENSED)\u201d without asking.",
          "next": "N_OUTCOME_CONFIRM_01"
        },
        {
          "id": "N_OUTCOME_CONFIRM_01",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
          "text": "The section is compiled, hole-punched and binder-ready. (pause)\nYou can almost hear someone else agreeing with it later because it\u2019s easier than disagreeing. (pause)\nYou stop one step short of calling it complete.",
          "next": "END_COMPILED"
        },
        {
          "id": "END_COMPILED",
          "type": "end",
          "outcomeId": "compile_evidence_packet",
          "effects": [
            {
              "key": "act3.evidencePacketCompiled",
              "action": "set",
              "value": true
            },
            {
              "key": "inventory.items",
              "action": "add",
              "value": "ITEM_EVIDENCE_PACKET_SECTION"
            },
            {
              "key": "paperwork.completeness",
              "action": "increment",
              "value": 2
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "id": "N_FAX_01",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
          "text": "You lift the handset and feed the first page like backing up your own conscience. (pause)\nThe machine whines. (pause)\nThe tray spits a status slip. Reassuring and useless. (pause)\n\u201cTRANSMISSION PARTIAL \u2014 RECEIPT SUCCESSFUL.\u201d (pause)\nYou did not create redundancy. You created another version of events.",
          "next": "PC_FAX_BACK"
        },
        {
          "id": "PC_FAX_BACK",
          "type": "player_choice",
          "speakerId": "PLAYER",
          "choices": [
            {
              "id": "LEAVE_BACK",
              "text": "leave: Put the handset back.",
              "next": "PC_MAIN_MENU"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "id": "N_LEAVE_01",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
          "text": "You step back. (pause) The copier\u2019s screen stays lit, holding your place in line. (pause)\nThe room does not forget unfinished tasks. (pause)\n\nNothing is compiled. (pause) Nothing is defensible yet.",
          "next": "END_NO_ACTION"
        },
        {
          "id": "END_NO_ACTION",
          "type": "end"
        }
      ]
    }
  ]
}